when leaving the using block above) might throw an exception when Close is
called in the Dispose function due to some communication issues. Why is this so
bad you might ask? The problem is if you get an exception inside of your using
block, if you get an exception there it would be "swallowed" by the exception
caused in the Dispose method. If you want to read about it more you can find
some information at the following locations:

 * Avoiding Problems with the Using Statement
   [http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/aa355056.aspx]
 * Blog discussing the issue
   [http://social.msdn.microsoft.com/Forums/en-US/wcf/thread/b95b91c7-d498-446c-b38f-ef132989c154]

